72
00:06:18,470 --> 00:06:23,330
That thing right there... is our dad.

73
00:06:24,620 --> 00:06:28,090
My dad needs these.

74
00:06:30,030 --> 00:06:32,090
Th-The bow and arrow...

75
00:06:33,350 --> 00:06:36,640
I want to find a Stand user for my dad's sake.

76
00:06:37,080 --> 00:06:39,190
That's why I can't let anyone else

77
00:06:39,190 --> 00:06:41,530
have this bow and arrow or destroy them,

78
00:06:41,530 --> 00:06:43,500
no matter what!

79
00:06:44,350 --> 00:06:46,260
Is it some kind of disease?

80
00:06:46,260 --> 00:06:48,240
Disease? No.

81
00:06:48,240 --> 00:06:51,270
My dad's perfectly healthy,

82
00:06:51,270 --> 00:06:53,510
and he's got an appetite.

83
00:06:53,900 --> 00:06:59,010
But he just keeps moaning, and he
doesn't recognize me as his son.

84
00:06:59,310 --> 00:07:03,060
So you were looking for a
Stand user to fix your dad.

85
00:07:03,130 --> 00:07:04,400
Fix?

86
00:07:05,870 --> 00:07:09,150
You gonna fix him for me?
That's not it, either.

87
00:07:15,550 --> 00:07:16,620
It's the opposite.

88
00:07:17,190 --> 00:07:22,830
I'm looking for a Stand user who'll kill my dad.

89
00:07:23,540 --> 00:07:25,900
Dad won't die, no matter what.

90
00:07:26,250 --> 00:07:28,060
Whether you smash his head in,

91
00:07:28,060 --> 00:07:32,840
or grind up his body, or rip
things off, nothing works!

92
00:07:36,440 --> 00:07:38,900
I just want to let him die normally.

93
00:07:39,210 --> 00:07:43,150
I swore when I was a kid that I'd do
anything to make that happen.

94
00:07:43,860 --> 00:07:47,350
And to do that, I need this bow and arrow.

95
00:07:47,970 --> 00:07:52,360
Otherwise, my dad will probably
live like this forever.

96
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:56,190
Because my dad had some
guy named Dio's cells

97
00:07:56,190 --> 00:07:59,790
implanted in his head,
so he ended up like this!

98
00:08:00,210 --> 00:08:02,740
Dio? Did you just say Dio?

99
00:08:02,740 --> 00:08:05,080
That's the guy Jotaro talked about.

100
00:08:07,270 --> 00:08:10,520
Let me tell you a bit about the past,

101
00:08:11,170 --> 00:08:12,680
Josuke Higashikata.

102
00:08:13,960 --> 00:08:18,310
After all, you're not completely uninvolved.

103
00:08:19,610 --> 00:08:24,570
Everything happened eleven
years ago, in 1988.

104
00:08:25,570 --> 00:08:29,070
At the time, I was seven,
and Okuyasu was four.

105
00:08:30,140 --> 00:08:32,250
We lived in Tokyo.

106
00:08:32,790 --> 00:08:36,210
The world was carefree,
thanks to the bubble economy,

107
00:08:36,210 --> 00:08:39,600
but at the time, my dad had no luck.

108
00:08:40,310 --> 00:08:42,280
Our mom died of an illness,

109
00:08:42,280 --> 00:08:44,620
the business that my dad
was running went under,

110
00:08:43,640 --> 00:08:48,120
Luxury Houses
Nijimura Land

111
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:46,910
and he was in massive debt.

112
00:08:51,190 --> 00:08:54,380
He would hit us for no reason all the time.

113
00:08:54,380 --> 00:08:57,010
Our dad was a total loser.

114
00:08:59,010 --> 00:09:00,930
But then, suddenly,

115
00:09:02,570 --> 00:09:06,310
money started rolling in to my dad.

116
00:09:06,830 --> 00:09:10,490
Even jewels and precious
metals, too, sometimes.

117
00:09:10,490 --> 00:09:13,030
He wasn't even really working.

118
00:09:14,810 --> 00:09:17,420
I found out later when I did some research

119
00:09:17,420 --> 00:09:22,420
that my dad had apparently
already sold his soul to Dio.

120
00:09:22,870 --> 00:09:25,720
He became one of his minions
in exchange for money.

121
00:09:27,970 --> 00:09:33,730
It seems that Dio was looking for anyone
with Stand potential back then.

122
00:09:33,730 --> 00:09:38,160
Somehow, he found out that
my dad had the potential,

123
00:09:38,670 --> 00:09:42,920
though I have no idea now
what his Stand was like.

124
00:09:43,610 --> 00:09:48,780
But one day... Even though it was ten
years ago, I still remember it vividly.

125
00:09:50,970 --> 00:09:55,740
When I got home from school, around 2:00 PM...

126
00:09:57,110 --> 00:09:58,130
Okuyasu!

127
00:09:59,780 --> 00:10:03,470
Did Dad hit you again? That scum!

128
00:10:03,470 --> 00:10:05,160
N-No!

129
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,250
Huh?

130
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:11,280
Dio...

131
00:10:12,380 --> 00:10:13,880
Dio's dead...

132
00:10:14,700 --> 00:10:16,660
That has to be why!

133
00:10:17,770 --> 00:10:18,800
Dad?

134
00:10:22,280 --> 00:10:24,570
Dad, let's call an ambulance.

135
00:10:24,570 --> 00:10:27,640
It's no use! This isn't an illness!

136
00:10:27,640 --> 00:10:30,140
The flesh bud has gone berserk!

137
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:33,610
I'm done for!

138
00:10:30,550 --> 00:10:31,680
Dad!

139
00:10:34,180 --> 00:10:39,250
About a year after that, he became
a glob of flesh that can't even tell

140
00:10:39,250 --> 00:10:41,450
that we're his sons anymore.

141
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:49,920
Dio would implant his own cells into
the heads of those he couldn't trust,

142
00:10:49,920 --> 00:10:52,250
and order them around when
he wanted to control them.

143
00:10:52,620 --> 00:10:56,140
Dad had one of those flesh buds
implanted in his head.

144
00:10:59,400 --> 00:11:02,140
I spent ten years researching everything.

145
00:11:02,520 --> 00:11:05,280
About Stands, about Jotaro...

146
00:11:05,890 --> 00:11:08,560
Then I found out about the
old woman named Enyaba,

147
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:11,230
and obtained the bow and arrow.

148
00:11:11,610 --> 00:11:14,050
But as I learned all of this,

149
00:11:14,050 --> 00:11:18,190
I also had to accept that
my dad would never recover.

150
00:11:19,210 --> 00:11:22,950
Because Dio's immortal cells
had become one with him.

151
00:11:23,690 --> 00:11:25,990
This is all he does, all day long.

152
00:11:25,990 --> 00:11:27,870
Every single day...

153
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:30,560
Day after day, for ten years,

154
00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:34,460
he uselessly scratches
around that box of junk.

155
00:11:34,920 --> 00:11:38,960
If I take the box away from him,
he just cries for days.

156
00:11:38,960 --> 00:11:40,640
It pisses me off.

157
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:45,510
Watching him just makes me
hate the idea of living.

158
00:11:47,570 --> 00:11:51,000
How many times have I told
you not to make a mess?

159
00:11:54,610 --> 00:11:59,160
He can be obedient if I discipline him,

160
00:11:59,650 --> 00:12:04,350
but he never stops digging
around in that box!

161
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:06,120
Bleh...

162
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:09,100
Hey! You're the one who needs to stop!

163
00:12:09,100 --> 00:12:11,100
He's your dad!

164
00:12:13,550 --> 00:12:14,900
Yeah, that's right.

165
00:12:14,900 --> 00:12:17,900
He's my father by blood.

166
00:12:18,280 --> 00:12:22,220
But right now, he's as much
my father as he's not.

167
00:12:22,600 --> 00:12:26,610
He's a man who sold his soul to Dio,
and got what he deserved.

168
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:29,720
Yet, on the other hand,

169
00:12:30,180 --> 00:12:35,410
do you know how it feels, not being able
to finish him off because he's your dad?

170
00:12:35,790 --> 00:12:40,030
That's exactly why I want him to die normally.

171
00:12:41,490 --> 00:12:45,710
Once he's finally dead,
my life can actually begin!

172
00:12:53,810 --> 00:12:57,150
Damn it! I told you to stop that!

173
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:58,820
It pisses me off!

174
00:12:59,540 --> 00:13:00,450
Hey!

175
00:13:00,860 --> 00:13:02,670
That's enough!

176
00:13:03,130 --> 00:13:05,970
I can't let you have this bow and arrow.

177
00:13:06,340 --> 00:13:07,550
No matter what!

178
00:13:07,550 --> 00:13:09,360
Don't get the wrong idea!

179
00:13:09,360 --> 00:13:11,390
I'll worry about the bow and arrow later.

180
00:13:12,950 --> 00:13:16,270
Right now, that box has my attention!

181
00:13:15,790 --> 00:13:16,940
Dogyaa

182
00:13:16,940 --> 00:13:18,690
Do

183
00:13:17,440 --> 00:13:18,690
Th-The box?

184
00:13:18,690 --> 00:13:19,940
gyaa

185
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,850
I saw him grabbing at some paper scraps,

186
00:13:33,850 --> 00:13:36,390
so I was curious about what it was.

187
00:13:37,480 --> 00:13:38,790
I see now.

188
00:13:47,830 --> 00:13:49,460
A family photo...

189
00:13:49,920 --> 00:13:52,170
S-So there was a reason.

190
00:13:52,560 --> 00:13:56,480
There was a reason for the
behavior he repeated for ten years.

191
00:13:56,710 --> 00:14:00,110
He was looking for the photo
of his sons at the time.

192
00:14:01,740 --> 00:14:04,430
He might not understand
what's going on right now,

193
00:14:04,430 --> 00:14:07,740
