230
00:16:38,150 --> 00:16:42,390
Okuyasu! Stop spacing out, you dumbass!

231
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:46,360
Big Bro!

232
00:16:47,210 --> 00:16:51,380
I'm taking this bow and
arrow, Keicho Nijimura!

233
00:16:51,380 --> 00:16:57,040
I, who got shot by this bow and arrow,
and had my Stand ability awakened!

234
00:16:57,040 --> 00:16:58,610
You think...

235
00:16:59,040 --> 00:17:02,080
someone like you can handle
this bow and arrow?

236
00:17:02,080 --> 00:17:03,910
Keicho Nijimura!

237
00:17:03,910 --> 00:17:06,160
You said Stands depend on
one's mentality, didn't you?

238
00:17:06,160 --> 00:17:08,210
Well, I've grown!

239
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:14,840
How else do you think my Stand,
Chili Pepper, grew this much?

240
00:17:14,840 --> 00:17:16,550
Worse Company!

241
00:17:16,550 --> 00:17:18,050
Shut up!

242
00:17:18,840 --> 00:17:19,890
Th-That's...

243
00:17:19,890 --> 00:17:21,130
Electricity!

244
00:17:21,130 --> 00:17:23,520
Okuyasu's big brother is being
turned into electricity,

245
00:17:23,970 --> 00:17:25,460
along with the bow and arrow!

246
00:17:25,460 --> 00:17:26,560
Big Bro!

247
00:17:26,560 --> 00:17:29,110
Don't touch me!

248
00:17:29,110 --> 00:17:32,890
You'll be dragged in, too!

249
00:17:33,360 --> 00:17:34,700
Big Bro...

250
00:17:34,890 --> 00:17:39,800
D-Damn it! It's taking the bow and arrow!

251
00:17:40,550 --> 00:17:41,720
Okuyasu...

252
00:17:42,390 --> 00:17:48,290
You were always holding me back!

253
00:17:50,960 --> 00:17:53,130
Big Bro!

254
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:57,680
Josuke!

255
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:06,200
I could have sworn I just saw
someone who looked like

256
00:18:06,200 --> 00:18:08,460
the user looking in through that window.

257
00:18:09,420 --> 00:18:12,240
Do you know anything about
that Stand we just saw, Okuyasu?

258
00:18:12,530 --> 00:18:19,240
N-No. My big bro found a lot of
Stand users I didn't know about.

259
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:24,500
J-Josuke! Th-That's...

260
00:18:37,100 --> 00:18:38,170
Okuyasu...

261
00:18:39,640 --> 00:18:44,240
My big bro... deserved to end up like that.

262
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:46,860
There's no way he could
have lived a decent life.

263
00:18:46,860 --> 00:18:48,640
That was his fate.

264
00:18:49,010 --> 00:18:50,650
But you know...

265
00:18:50,650 --> 00:18:53,220
In the end, my big bro...

266
00:18:53,220 --> 00:18:57,700
In the very end, my big bro
defended me, didn't he?

267
00:18:57,970 --> 00:19:00,830
Josuke, you saw it, right?

268
00:19:01,700 --> 00:19:03,950
Yeah. I definitely saw it.

269
00:19:04,680 --> 00:19:07,970
Your big bro defended you.

270
00:19:30,220 --> 00:19:33,230
Is this Jotaro Kujo?

271
00:19:34,730 --> 00:19:36,300
I don't recognize your voice.

272
00:19:36,300 --> 00:19:38,200
Who are you?

273
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,860
That doesn't matter.

274
00:19:39,860 --> 00:19:45,780
Jotaro Kujo, I'm asking
you to leave Morioh City.

275
00:19:46,350 --> 00:19:48,510
I don't think I'll listen to someone

276
00:19:48,510 --> 00:19:51,280
I don't know suddenly telling me to leave.

277
00:19:51,870 --> 00:19:54,630
Would you leave, no questions asked,
if you were in my shoes?

278
00:19:54,630 --> 00:19:56,920
I'm the one who has the bow and arrow.

279
00:19:58,130 --> 00:20:02,670
I got it after I killed Keicho Nijimura.

280
00:20:02,670 --> 00:20:06,820
I don't mind killing you either,
Jotaro, but I hear that

281
00:20:06,820 --> 00:20:10,920
you have the ability to stop
time for a second or two.

282
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:13,460
You sound like a tough opponent,

283
00:20:13,460 --> 00:20:16,420
so I thought I'd give you
a call and warn you first.

284
00:20:16,420 --> 00:20:18,240
Are you also Stand user?

285
00:20:18,640 --> 00:20:20,700
What do you plan to do
with the bow and arrow?

286
00:20:20,700 --> 00:20:23,990
I don't plan on giving you any trouble.

287
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:27,470
And as long as Josuke Higashikata
doesn't try anything,

288
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:29,570
Unavailable Number  Public Phone

289
00:20:27,470 --> 00:20:29,580
I won't do anything to him, either.

290
00:20:29,950 --> 00:20:33,300
I just received this Stand ability.

291
00:20:33,300 --> 00:20:36,260
I just want to have a little fun.

292
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:40,950
I'm fed up with my annoying life of
entrance exams and getting a job.

293
00:20:40,950 --> 00:20:42,380
Are you a student?

294
00:20:43,090 --> 00:20:44,910
What difference does that make?!

295
00:20:44,910 --> 00:20:48,560
Listen! If you overstay
your welcome in my city,

296
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:51,730
I'm gonna kill you and Josuke, too! Got it?!

297
00:20:49,680 --> 00:20:51,730
How many other Stand users are in this city?

298
00:21:08,010 --> 00:21:09,730
Good grief...

299
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:15,010
Keicho Nijimura was buried
in Kunimi Peak Cemetery,

300
00:21:15,010 --> 00:21:17,290
which is west of Morioh City.

301
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:21,520
The stolen bow and arrow remain missing.

302
00:21:18,250 --> 00:21:22,260
Nijimura Family

303
00:21:22,560 --> 00:21:25,490
Okuyasu Nijimura decided to settle down

304
00:21:25,490 --> 00:21:27,760
with his father in Morioh City for a while.

305
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:29,410
And...

306
00:21:33,390 --> 00:21:35,300
Josuke, would you get that?

307
00:21:37,870 --> 00:21:39,080
Yes?

308
00:21:40,340 --> 00:21:43,490
Hey, Josuke! Let's go to school.

309
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:44,820
Huh?

310
00:21:44,820 --> 00:21:48,610
I'll be going to the same school
as you starting today.

311
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:51,190
Even so, you don't have to come and get me.

312
00:21:51,190 --> 00:21:53,440
We're not in grade school.

313
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:57,990
Man, I had no idea your house was,
like, right in front of mine!

314
00:21:57,990 --> 00:22:01,010
Yeah, you could call that a shocking truth...

315
00:22:01,010 --> 00:22:03,200
Come on. Let's hurry up and go.

316
00:22:03,200 --> 00:22:05,470
Oh, is that a friend of yours, Josuke?

317
00:22:05,470 --> 00:22:08,290
Hi! I'm Okuyasu Nijimura!

318
00:22:08,290 --> 00:22:11,270
Come on in and have a cup of coffee
while he finishes getting ready.

319
00:22:11,270 --> 00:22:13,970
Really? Thank you very much!

